    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with a high-ceiling lineup led by **Christian Yelich** (72.61) and **Trea Turner** (71.43). **Christian Yelich** thrives in a favorable matchup against Littell, where a significant platoon edge (+13%) and optimal order placement anchor his status as our primary producer. Meanwhile, **Trea Turner** maintains his elite status despite facing a formidable Gallen; his leadoff role (+10%) provides the necessary floor to balance the risk of a high-skill opponent. **Kyle Schwarber** also stands out, with his elite xwOBA (.402) helping him weather the Gallen matchup, resulting in a strong 67.82 score. We are aggressively targeting stolen base opportunities today, evidenced by **Caleb Durbin** (64.76) and his 85% SB-friendly delivery profile, further buoyed by a +5% wind-out advantage that inflates his scoring potential.\n\nOur most difficult bench decision involved **Jerar Encarnacion**, who carried a respectable 56.19 score but was ultimately squeezed out of the starting nine. While his park factors are excellent (+16%), his lower slot in the order (-6%) and the overall efficiency of our starting outfield\u2014specifically **Josh Smith** and **Pete Crow-Armstrong**\u2014made him the odd man out. **Pete Crow-Armstrong** remains a high-variance play; while his SP skill adjustment is negative, the +14% platoon edge and the wind-out bonus justify his inclusion over the consistency of **Jerar Encarnacion** or the high-speed potential of **Victor Scott II** (55.66). We are closely monitoring **Yordan Alvarez** (55.60), who faces an elite arm in Gilbert; his score is suppressed by a harsh -19% SP skill penalty, but his historical BvP and +8% order premium keep him in the lineup to avoid leaving elite contact potential on the bench.",
